{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "doctor365-telemedicine-complete-v1-1",
    "name": "Doctor365 Telemedicine Service - Complete Setup (v1.1 Updated)",
    "description": "Complete API collection for Doctor365 Telemedicine Service with Jitsi Cloud (8x8.vc) integration. UPDATED: New validation, error codes, and response structures.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00. Setup & Configuration",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "README - Start Here (v1.1 Updated)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://postman-echo.com/get",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["postman-echo", "com"],
              "path": ["get"]
            },
            "description": "## Doctor365 Telemedicine Service - Updated April 8, 2026\n\n### ✨ What's New in v1.1:\n- ✅ New error codes: INVALID_APPOINTMENT_ID, INVALID_SESSION_ID, INVALID_AUTH_FORMAT, NO_AUTH_HEADER, TOKEN_EXPIRED\n- ✅ Validation: ObjectId format checking for appointment/session IDs\n- ✅ Enhanced response: endSession now returns consultationSummary\n- ✅ Better error messages: Include role and status context\n- ✅ New tests: Format validation, state transitions, auth errors\n\n### Setup Instructions:\n1. Import Environment: `Doctor365_Telemedicine_Environment.postman_environment.json`\n2. Select Environment: Top-right dropdown\n3. Start Service: `npm run dev`\n4. Generate Tokens: Go to \"01. Generate Test Tokens\"\n5. Follow numbered folders sequentially\n\n### New Error Codes to Expect:\n- INVALID_APPOINTMENT_ID: Appointment ID not MongoDB ObjectId format\n- INVALID_SESSION_ID: Session ID not MongoDB ObjectId format\n- INVALID_AUTH_FORMAT: Missing 'Bearer ' prefix\n- NO_AUTH_HEADER: Missing Authorization header\n- TOKEN_EXPIRED: JWT has expired\n- INVALID_TOKEN: JWT is invalid\n- CONFLICT: Resource already exists (409)\n- NOT_FOUND: Resource not found (404)\n- FORBIDDEN: Permission denied (includes role)\n- INVALID_STATE: Cannot transition state (includes current status)\n- VALIDATION_ERROR: Required fields violated\n"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Service Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{service_url}}/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost:5005"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verify service is running and MongoDB is connected"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "01. Generate Test Tokens",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Generate Doctor Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  let response = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.environment.set('doctor_token', response.token);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('doctor_id', response.payload.userId);",
                  "  pm.test('Doctor token generated successfully', function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(response.token).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(response.payload.userId).to.equal('doc-001');",
                  "  });",
                  "  console.log('✅ Doctor token: ' + response.token.substring(0, 20) + '...');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"userId\": \"doc-001\",\"email\": \"doctor@hospital.com\",\"role\": \"doctor\",\"name\": \"Dr. Sarah Johnson\"}"},
            "url": {"raw": "{{service_url}}/generate-token", "host": ["localhost:5005"], "path": ["generate-token"]},
            "description": "Generate JWT token for doctor. Used for testing doctor-only endpoints."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Generate Patient Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  let response = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.environment.set('patient_token', response.token);",
                  "  pm.environment.set('patient_id', response.payload.userId);",
                  "  pm.test('Patient token generated successfully', function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(response.token).to.exist;",
                  "    pm.expect(response.payload.userId).to.equal('pat-001');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"userId\": \"pat-001\",\"email\": \"patient@email.com\",\"role\": \"patient\",\"name\": \"John Doe\"}"},
            "url": {"raw": "{{service_url}}/generate-token", "host": ["localhost:5005"], "path": ["generate-token"]},
            "description": "Generate JWT token for patient. Used for testing patient access restrictions."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02. Create Session",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "✅ Create Session (Success)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "let response = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Response code is 201 Created', function() { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(201); });",
                  "pm.test('Session has valid structure', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(response.data).to.have.all.keys('sessionId', 'appointmentId', 'doctorId', 'patientId', 'meetingLink', 'meetingRoomId', 'meetingProvider', 'status', 'createdAt');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Status is scheduled', function() { pm.expect(response.data.status).to.equal('scheduled'); });",
                  "pm.test('Meeting link contains 8x8.vc', function() { pm.expect(response.data.meetingLink).to.include('8x8.vc'); });",
                  "pm.environment.set('session_id', response.data.sessionId);",
                  "pm.environment.set('meeting_link', response.data.meetingLink);",
                  "console.log('✅ Session created: ' + response.data.sessionId);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"},
              {"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{doctor_token}}"}
            ],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"appointmentId\": \"507f1f77bcf86cd799439011\",\"patientId\": \"pat-001\",\"notes\": \"\"}"},
            "url": {"raw": "{{service_url}}/api/telemedicine/sessions", "host": ["localhost:5005"], "path": ["api", "telemedicine", "sessions"]},
            "description": "Create new telemedicine session. Doctor authorization required. Generates unique meeting link with 8x8.vc and JWT token."
          }
        },
